article.headline: North Florida 78, Stetson 66
article.story: JACKSONVILLE, Fla. -- Eni Cuka had 21 points and three other North Florida players scored in double figures in a 78-66 win over Stetson on Saturday. Cuka went 5-for-10 from beyond the arc in the game for the Ospreys (8-20, 6-12 Atlantic Sun Conference). Cortez Riley added 15 points, Zack Riggins had 12 and Stan Januska tallied 11. The Ospreys have won three games in a row and swept the season series with the Hatters, thanks to a 55-53 win in DeLand, Fla. on Jan. 25. Garfield Blair led the Hatters (13-14, 9-9) with 26 points, while A.J. Smith had 16 and Kris Thomas added 12. Stetson never led after an early 3-2 advantage in the first half. The Ospreys shot 54.8 percent from the field (23 of 42) en route to victory compared to the Hatters, who shot 41.5 percent (22 of 53).
